=head1 NAME

password.cgi - Secure password storage and authentication with legacy MD5 migration

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This CGI script provides secure password authentication using Argon2id as the
primary hashing algorithm, with transparent migration from legacy MD5 hashes.

=head1 SECURITY ARCHITECTURE

=over 4

=item * B<Primary hash>: Argon2id (memory-hard, resistant to GPU/ASIC attacks)

=item * B<Legacy support>: MD5 hashes are verified and immediately migrated to Argon2id on successful login

=item * B<MD5 hashes are never created for new passwords> - only used for reading existing legacy data

=item * B<CSRF protection>: Cryptographically random tokens validated on all POST requests

=item * B<Rate limiting>: 5 failed attempts per 15-minute window per username/IP

=item * B<Session security>: HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookies with session regeneration

=item * B<Timing attack resistance>: Constant-time comparison and dummy hashing for unknown users

=item * B<Automatic parameter upgrade>: Rehashes when Argon2 parameters are strengthened

=back

=head1 DATABASE SCHEMA

    CREATE TABLE users (
        username             VARCHAR(255) PRIMARY KEY,
        password_hash_argon2 TEXT,
        password_hash_md5    VARCHAR(32),
        hash_algorithm       VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'md5',
        account_locked       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
        password_updated_at  TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE,
        created_at           TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
    );

    CREATE TABLE login_attempts (
        id           SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
        username     VARCHAR(255),
        ip_address   VARCHAR(45),
        success      BOOLEAN NOT NULL,
        attempted_at TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
    );
    CREATE INDEX idx_login_attempts_lookup ON login_attempts (username, ip_address, attempted_at);

    CREATE TABLE security_audit_log (
        id          SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
        username    VARCHAR(255),
        event_type  VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
        details     TEXT,
        ip_address  VARCHAR(45),
        created_at  TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE DEFAULT NOW()
    );

=cut